The paper deals with privacy in machine learning, specifically in the context of stochastic gradient descent (SGD). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses differential privacy, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The empirical analysis and experiments involve large-scale datasets and statistical analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a method to improve the privacy-utility trade-off, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
